Hello Stanislav,

Thank you for all the great work you've done!

There are currently 2 "active" developers on the project, but none of
us really have time to look at the code. We get quite a lot of monitor
support requests, but that's about it. So it's good for the project
when more experienced Linux users have a look at all the bits and
pieces that don't work perfectly.

As they say, every little detail counts.

If you are interested in becoming a developer/maintainer for
ddccontrol, we'll gladly accept your help.

Lately, we were trying to come up with a solution to (more or less)
automatically handle monitor support requests. As I said before, we
haven't really had time to think about it, but if you think of
something, feel free to let us know. Anyways, adding full support for
a monitor is quite a lot of work, and still needs documentation and
expertise.

Thank you again for your work, and keep it up if you can.

Cheers,
William

